The paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms for image classification and prioritization, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the algorithm's effectiveness and impact on workflow also involves statistical analysis and simulation, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of false negative predictions, which could also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
